How to create a new version of sumo
-----------------------------------

* Ensure that all the tests work
  (chdir test && make distclean && make)

* Save the state of the mq queue

  hg qcommit -m backup

* Go to the administration directory:

  cd administration_tools

* There review all the changes.

* Then show the current version number:

  ./show-version.sh

* Create a new version with:

  ./new-version.sh [NUMBER]

* convert mq patches

  hg qfinish -a

* create a new tag
  show tags with 
    hg tags | head
  create tag with
    hg tag [TAG]

* Create documentation

  ./doc-rebuild.sh

* Clean distribution directories

  ./cleanup-distdirs.sh

* Create distribution tar files

  ./mk-dist.sh

* Create debian packages

  ./docker-run.sh debian-7
  within run: cd /root/sumo/administration_tools && ./mk-deb.sh

  ./docker-run.sh debian-8
  within run: cd /root/sumo/administration_tools && ./mk-deb.sh

  ./docker-run.sh debian-9
  within run: cd /root/sumo/administration_tools && ./mk-deb.sh

  ./docker-run.sh fedora-25
  within run: cd /root/sumo/administration_tools && ./mk-rpm.sh

  ./docker-run.sh fedora-26
  within run: cd /root/sumo/administration_tools && ./mk-rpm.sh

  ./docker-run.sh fedora-27
  within run: cd /root/sumo/administration_tools && ./mk-rpm.sh

* push changes to local repo

  hg push

* upload docs to sourceforge

  ./sourceforge-upload-html.sh

* upload dist files to sourceforge

  ./sourceforge-upload-distfiles.sh

* push changes to sourceforge

  ./sourceforge-push.sh

  
